# TinyTest

This project uses **TinyTest** for testing. Do NOT use PHPUnit-style assertions (`$this->assertEquals()`). TinyTest uses plain global functions like `assert_eq($actual, $expected, "message")`.

## Running Tests

```bash
php {{TINYTEST_PATH}}/tinytest.php -f tests/test_foo.php        # single file
php {{TINYTEST_PATH}}/tinytest.php -d tests/                    # directory
php {{TINYTEST_PATH}}/tinytest.php -f tests/test_foo.php -t test_name  # single test
php {{TINYTEST_PATH}}/tinytest.php -v -f tests/test_foo.php     # verbose (stack traces)
php {{TINYTEST_PATH}}/tinytest.php -j -f tests/test_foo.php     # JSON output
phpdbg -qrr -d xdebug.mode=off {{TINYTEST_PATH}}/tinytest.php -j -c -d tests/  # JSON + coverage (shows uncovered functions)
```

## Skills

### Utilities
- `/test-run` — run tests and report results (file, directory, or single test)
- `/test-fix` — diagnose and fix a failing test
- `/test-report` — read-only project coverage dashboard: per-file health, failing/incomplete tests, unresolved annotations (requires phpdbg)

### Single File
- `/test-generate <file>` — generate an initial test file for a PHP source file (includes full assertion/annotation reference)
- `/test-improve <file>` — review an existing test file for quality issues: weak assertions, PHPUnit drift, incomplete tests, anti-patterns — then fix them
- `/test-cover-file <file>` — achieve full coverage for one file: functions first, then every reachable line and branch (requires phpdbg)

### Single Function
- `/test-analyze <file> <function>` — deep-analyze one function: trace all paths, find callers, classify bugs, generate exhaustive tests
- `/test-regression <function> "<bug description>"` — write a regression test for a known bug

### Project-Wide
- `/test-bootstrap` — scan all source files, register new ones in test_sources.md, generate initial test files for each
- `/test-audit` — full coverage audit: find every uncovered function, analyze in context, generate tests, produce bug/smell report (requires phpdbg)

### Refactoring & Adoption
- `/test-refactor <file>` — extract untestable business logic into pure functions and generate tests for them
- `/test-migrate <file|dir>` — migrate PHPUnit test files to TinyTest (structural conversion, assertion remapping, mock files)

## Quick Reference

- Test files: `test_*.php`, test functions: `test_*`/`it_*`/`should_*`, all in global namespace
- Assertions: `assert_eq`, `assert_true`, `assert_false`, `assert_contains`, etc. — see `{{TINYTEST_PATH}}/assertions.php` for full list
- Parameter order: actual before expected, haystack before needle, message always last
- A test with no assertions is marked incomplete ("IN") and counts as a failure
